<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.63.8_0001" />

<fw type="curatorial">8</fw>

<fw type="authorial">(1)</fw>
<opener>
<dateline>
5835 Vine St.<lb/>
Lincoln, Neb.<lb/>
68505<lb/>
-----<lb/>

1-26-'72
</dateline>

<salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
</opener>
<p>We have been reading aloud from your Biography, and I want to tell you how it strikes us after a considerable interval. We not only enjoyed it, but we greatly admire it.</p>

<note type="authorial">(over)</note>

<pb facs="nei.j4c.63.8_0002"/>
<fw type="authorial"><del>-3-</del>-2-</fw>

<p>Your comment on the lyrics is bully, and your analysis is excellent.</p>

<p>I'm interested in the U. of Mo. Press, but I am hoping the widespread popularity of <hi rend="underline">Black Elk</hi>, the <hi rend="underline">Pocket Book</hi>, and the publication of my Autobiography</p>

<fw type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER</hi></fw>

</div1>
</body>

